<a name="Getting_Started"></a><h2>Getting Started</h2>
<a name="Installing_the_Game"></a><h3>Installing the Game</h3>
<p>You should install the Doom 3 engine game into a directory with no spaces (with Doom 3 the folder could be "d:\doom3") to avoid potential problems later on. 
</p>
<a name="Base_and_Mod_Directories"></a><h3>Base and Mod Directories</h3>
<p>Although you can work in the game base directory it's strongly recommended that you create a new mod directory (eg "d:\doom3\mymod") to keep the Doom 3 base folder clean of custom files. It should only contain the original <a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/PK4_%28file_format%29" title="PK4 (file format)">.PK4</a> files and the directories created at runtime by Doom 3.
</p><p><i>Add information about Base, Add-on Folder (fs_game_base) and Modfolder Directories</i>
</p>
<div><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" class="image" title="Image:D3square_25.png"><img src="/web/20070729231805im_/http://www.modwiki.net/w/images/2/23/D3square_25.png" alt="Image:D3square_25.png" width="25" height="25" longdesc="/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" /></a> <b>Note:</b> Doom 3 only: <dl><dd><i>doom3/base/</i></dd></dl></div>
<div><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" class="image" title="Image:D3square_25.png"><img src="/web/20070729231805im_/http://www.modwiki.net/w/images/2/23/D3square_25.png" alt="Image:D3square_25.png" width="25" height="25" longdesc="/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" /></a> <b>Note:</b> Doom 3: ROE only: <dl><dd><i>doom3/d3xp/ (add-on folder)</i></dd></dl></div>
<div><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image:Q4square_25.png" class="image" title="Image:Q4square_25.png"><img src="/web/20070729231805im_/http://www.modwiki.net/w/images/e/e8/Q4square_25.png" alt="Image:Q4square_25.png" width="25" height="25" longdesc="/wiki/Image:Q4square_25.png" /></a> <b>Note:</b> Quake 4 only: <dl><dd><i>quake4/q4base/</i></dd></dl></div>
<a name="Starting_your_Mod"></a><h3>Starting your Mod</h3>
<p>You can create shortcuts to get into the editor or game quickly:
</p>
<pre>testing: d:\doom3\doom3.exe +set fs_game mymod 
</pre>
<p>If you use <a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Antialiasing" title="Antialiasing">antialiasing</a> in Doom 3 you'll want to add "+set <a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/R_multiSamples_%28cvar%29" title="R multiSamples (cvar)">r_multisamples</a> 0" at the end of the editing shortcut and "+set r_multisamples X" at the end of the testing shortcut (if you wish to keep using AntiAliasing in-game). Make sure you substitute the X with the number of samples you use (2, 4, 8, 16).
</p>
<div><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" class="image" title="Image:D3square_25.png"><img src="/web/20070729231805im_/http://www.modwiki.net/w/images/2/23/D3square_25.png" alt="Image:D3square_25.png" width="25" height="25" longdesc="/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" /></a> <b>Note:</b> Doom 3: ROE only: <dl><dd><i>If you are modding for the Doom 3: Resurrection of Evil expansion then add "+set fs_game_base d3xp" at the end of both shortcuts.</i></dd></dl></div>
<div><a href="/web/20070729231805/http://www.modwiki.net/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" class="image" title="Image:D3square_25.png"><img src="/web/20070729231805im_/http://www.modwiki.net/w/images/2/23/D3square_25.png" alt="Image:D3square_25.png" width="25" height="25" longdesc="/wiki/Image:D3square_25.png" /></a> <b>Note:</b> Doom 3 only: <dl><dd><i>Pre-1.3 versions of Doom 3 would copy your "doomkey" (and "xpkey" if you have the Doom 3: Resurrection of Evil expansion) file to all your mod folders. This means you have to be careful that you do NOT distribute this file along with your mod if you are still using these older versions of the game. Even if you upgraded to v1.3 you should make sure your mod folder does not have this file.</i></dd></dl></div>
<a name="Beginning_Editing"></a><h2>Beginning Editing</h2>
